The images contained in the collage are copyright © to the BBC, but it is believed that they are covered by the U.S. fair use law because: 
                    The images in question are low-resolution copies of publicity photographs released between 1963 and 2014;
                    The images are being used to identify and for informational purposes about the lead character ("the Doctor") from Doctor Who;
                    The images are significant because they demonstrate the changing nature of the character in the programme's long history;
                    The use of the images in these articles will have no effect on the BBC's commercial use of the images in question.
